<head>BLESS</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>BLESSING</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">保佑</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PRAISE SUPERNATURALLY AND HELP SUPERNATURALLY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[PRACTICAL/VERBAL]</p>
<p>1. Yòu 右／佑／祐 refers to the active blessings conferred on humans by the spirits or gods.</p>
<p>[PRACTICAL]</p>
<p>2. Zhù 祝 refers to the use of language to enlist the spirits in support for someone, and in a broader sense the word can refer to the formal expression of good wishes for someone on festive occasions.</p>
<p>[VERBAL]</p>
        </div>
